Vice President Biden met with Deputy Prime Minister of the United Kingdom Nick Clegg to discuss various issues, including the need for diplomacy with the new leadership in Iran. They also discussed the situation in Syria and agreed on the importance of a UN Security Council Resolution to ensure the Assad regime's compliance with chemical weapons commitments. Both leaders expressed support for a political solution and a negotiated transition in Syria. They also discussed the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership negotiations, which could create more jobs through increased trade and investment between the U.S. and the EU. The Vice President reiterated U.S. support for the all-party talks in Northern Ireland and the progress towards a united community and shared future.